data.name: Crispy Fried Fish

ingredients.name: white fish fillets (like cod or tilapia)

data.quickTastyDescription: Golden and crispy fish fillets that are tender on the inside, perfect with a squeeze of lemon!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix together the flour, cornmeal, salt, and pepper.
In another bowl, whisk together the egg and milk.
Dip each fish fillet first into the egg mixture, then coat with the flour mixture, pressing lightly to adhere.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Fry the fish fillets in batches for about 3-4 minutes on each side or until golden brown and cooked through.
Remove from the skillet and place on paper towels to drain excess oil.
